{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":960,"text":"I was a blue-eyed,\nchubby-cheeked five-year-old"},{"time":3640,"text":"when I joined my family\non the picket line for the first time."},{"time":7840,"text":"My mom made me leave\nmy dolls in the minivan."},{"time":10800,"text":"I'd stand on a street corner\nin the heavy Kansas humidity,"},{"time":13920,"text":"surrounded by a few dozen relatives,"},{"time":16560,"text":"with my tiny fists clutching\na sign that I couldn't read yet:"},{"time":20680,"text":"\"Gays are worthy of death.\""},{"time":23120,"text":"This was the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25040,"text":"Our protests soon became\na daily occurrence"},{"time":27280,"text":"and an international phenomenon,"},{"time":29240,"text":"and as a member\nof Westboro Baptist Church,"},{"time":31720,"text":"I became a fixture\non picket lines across the country."},{"time":34880,"text":"The end of my antigay picketing career"},{"time":37240,"text":"and life as I knew it,"},{"time":38680,"text":"came 20 years later,"},{"time":40360,"text":"triggered in part by strangers on Twitter"},{"time":42880,"text":"who showed me the power\nof engaging the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47280,"text":"In my home,"},{"time":48520,"text":"life was framed as an epic\nspiritual battle between good and evil."},{"time":52200,"text":"The good was my church and its members,"},{"time":54800,"text":"and the evil was everyone else."},{"time":57880,"text":"My church's antics were such"},{"time":59360,"text":"that we were constantly\nat odds with the world,"},{"time":61800,"text":"and that reinforced\nour otherness on a daily basis."},{"time":65640,"text":"\"Make a difference\nbetween the unclean and the clean,\""},{"time":68280,"text":"the verse says,"},{"time":69640,"text":"and so we did."},{"time":71000,"text":"From baseball games to military funerals,"},{"time":73160,"text":"we trekked across the country\nwith neon protest signs in hand"},{"time":76960,"text":"to tell others exactly\nhow \"unclean\" they were"},{"time":79960,"text":"and exactly why\nthey were headed for damnation."},{"time":83440,"text":"This was the focus of our whole lives."},{"time":86400,"text":"This was the only way for me to do good\nin a world that sits in Satan's lap."},{"time":91360,"text":"And like the rest of my 10 siblings,"},{"time":93360,"text":"I believed what I was taught\nwith all my heart,"},{"time":95840,"text":"and I pursued Westboro's agenda\nwith a special sort of zeal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"In 2009, that zeal brought me to Twitter."},{"time":103560,"text":"Initially, the people\nI encountered on the platform"},{"time":106000,"text":"were just as hostile as I expected."},{"time":108240,"text":"They were the digital version\nof the screaming hordes"},{"time":110760,"text":"I'd been seeing at protests\nsince I was a kid."},{"time":113440,"text":"But in the midst of that digital brawl,"},{"time":115920,"text":"a strange pattern developed."},{"time":118280,"text":"Someone would arrive at my profile\nwith the usual rage and scorn,"},{"time":122960,"text":"I would respond with a custom mix\nof Bible verses, pop culture references"},{"time":127120,"text":"and smiley faces."},{"time":129479,"text":"They would be understandably\nconfused and caught off guard,"},{"time":133640,"text":"but then a conversation would ensue."},{"time":136120,"text":"And it was civil --"},{"time":137400,"text":"full of genuine curiosity on both sides."},{"time":140360,"text":"How had the other come to such\noutrageous conclusions about the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145120,"text":"Sometimes the conversation\neven bled into real life."},{"time":148160,"text":"People I'd sparred with on Twitter"},{"time":149840,"text":"would come out\nto the picket line to see me"},{"time":152200,"text":"when I protested in their city."},{"time":154840,"text":"A man named David was one such person."},{"time":157520,"text":"He ran a blog called \"Jewlicious,\""},{"time":160800,"text":"and after several months\nof heated but friendly arguments online,"},{"time":163920,"text":"he came out to see me\nat a picket in New Orleans."},{"time":166920,"text":"He brought me a Middle Eastern dessert\nfrom Jerusalem, where he lives,"},{"time":170600,"text":"and I brought him kosher chocolate"},{"time":172880,"text":"and held a \"God hates Jews\" sign."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":177040,"text":"There was no confusion\nabout our positions,"},{"time":179120,"text":"but the line between friend and foe\nwas becoming blurred."},{"time":182800,"text":"We'd started to see each other\nas human beings,"},{"time":185080,"text":"and it changed the way\nwe spoke to one another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188280,"text":"It took time,"},{"time":189520,"text":"but eventually these conversations\nplanted seeds of doubt in me."},{"time":193080,"text":"My friends on Twitter took the time\nto understand Westboro's doctrines,"},{"time":196760,"text":"and in doing so,"},{"time":198000,"text":"they were able to find inconsistencies\nI'd missed my entire life."},{"time":202120,"text":"Why did we advocate\nthe death penalty for gays"},{"time":205040,"text":"when Jesus said, \"Let he who is\nwithout sin cast the first stone?\""},{"time":209280,"text":"How could we claim to love our neighbor"},{"time":211760,"text":"while at the same time\npraying for God to destroy them?"},{"time":215880,"text":"The truth is that the care shown to me\nby these strangers on the internet"},{"time":219720,"text":"was itself a contradiction."},{"time":222200,"text":"It was growing evidence"},{"time":223480,"text":"that people on the other side were not\nthe demons I'd been led to believe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228200,"text":"These realizations were life-altering."},{"time":231240,"text":"Once I saw that we were not\nthe ultimate arbiters of divine truth"},{"time":234520,"text":"but flawed human beings,"},{"time":236320,"text":"I couldn't pretend otherwise."},{"time":238440,"text":"I couldn't justify our actions --"},{"time":240920,"text":"especially our cruel practice\nof protesting funerals"},{"time":243920,"text":"and celebrating human tragedy."},{"time":247520,"text":"These shifts in my perspective"},{"time":249000,"text":"contributed to a larger erosion\nof trust in my church,"},{"time":252120,"text":"and eventually it made it\nimpossible for me to stay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256680,"text":"In spite of overwhelming grief and terror,\nI left Westboro in 2012."},{"time":262760,"text":"In those days just after I left,"},{"time":264680,"text":"the instinct to hide\nwas almost paralyzing."},{"time":268240,"text":"I wanted to hide\nfrom the judgement of my family,"},{"time":270600,"text":"who I knew would never\nspeak to me again --"},{"time":272840,"text":"people whose thoughts and opinions\nhad meant everything to me."},{"time":276280,"text":"And I wanted to hide from the world\nI'd rejected for so long --"},{"time":279680,"text":"people who had no reason at all\nto give me a second chance"},{"time":282440,"text":"after a lifetime of antagonism."},{"time":285600,"text":"And yet, unbelievably,"},{"time":287200,"text":"they did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288680,"text":"The world had access to my past\nbecause it was all over the internet --"},{"time":292080,"text":"thousands of tweets\nand hundreds of interviews,"},{"time":294480,"text":"everything from local TV news\nto \"The Howard Stern Show\" --"},{"time":298000,"text":"but so many embraced me\nwith open arms anyway."},{"time":301800,"text":"I wrote an apology\nfor the harm I'd caused,"},{"time":303920,"text":"but I also knew that an apology\ncould never undo any of it."},{"time":307960,"text":"All I could do was try to build a new life"},{"time":310240,"text":"and find a way somehow\nto repair some of the damage."},{"time":314560,"text":"People had every reason\nto doubt my sincerity,"},{"time":316960,"text":"but most of them didn't."},{"time":318880,"text":"And --"},{"time":320680,"text":"given my history,"},{"time":321920,"text":"it was more than I could've hoped for --"},{"time":323880,"text":"forgiveness and the benefit of the doubt."},{"time":326360,"text":"It still amazes me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328520,"text":"I spent my first year away from home"},{"time":332480,"text":"adrift with my younger sister,"},{"time":334200,"text":"who had chosen to leave with me."},{"time":336800,"text":"We walked into an abyss,"},{"time":338360,"text":"but we were shocked to find\nthe light and a way forward"},{"time":342080,"text":"in the same communities\nwe'd targeted for so long."},{"time":345600,"text":"David,"},{"time":346840,"text":"my \"Jewlicious\" friend from Twitter,"},{"time":348760,"text":"invited us to spend time among\na Jewish community in Los Angeles."},{"time":352520,"text":"We slept on couches in the home\nof a Hasidic rabbi and his wife"},{"time":355760,"text":"and their four kids --"},{"time":357600,"text":"the same rabbi that I'd protested\nthree years earlier"},{"time":360440,"text":"with a sign that said,\n\"Your rabbi is a whore.\""},{"time":364920,"text":"We spent long hours talking\nabout theology and Judaism and life"},{"time":368880,"text":"while we washed dishes\nin their kosher kitchen"},{"time":371120,"text":"and chopped vegetables for dinner."},{"time":373600,"text":"They treated us like family."},{"time":375640,"text":"They held nothing against us,"},{"time":377760,"text":"and again I was astonished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380760,"text":"That period was full of turmoil,"},{"time":382480,"text":"but one part I've returned to often"},{"time":384800,"text":"is a surprising realization\nI had during that time --"},{"time":388520,"text":"that it was a relief and a privilege\nto let go of the harsh judgments"},{"time":392800,"text":"that instinctively ran through my mind\nabout nearly every person I saw."},{"time":397680,"text":"I realized that now I needed to learn."},{"time":401040,"text":"I needed to listen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403520,"text":"This has been at the front\nof my mind lately,"},{"time":405680,"text":"because I can't help but see\nin our public discourse"},{"time":408640,"text":"so many of the same destructive impulses\nthat ruled my former church."},{"time":413560,"text":"We celebrate tolerance and diversity\nmore than at any other time in memory,"},{"time":417520,"text":"and still we grow more and more divided."},{"time":420440,"text":"We want good things --"},{"time":422360,"text":"justice, equality,\nfreedom, dignity, prosperity --"},{"time":426000,"text":"but the path we've chosen"},{"time":427320,"text":"looks so much like the one\nI walked away from four years ago."},{"time":431360,"text":"We've broken the world into us and them,"},{"time":434520,"text":"only emerging from our bunkers long enough"},{"time":436600,"text":"to lob rhetorical grenades\nat the other camp."},{"time":439840,"text":"We write off half the country\nas out-of-touch liberal elites"},{"time":443560,"text":"or racist misogynist bullies."},{"time":446200,"text":"No nuance, no complexity, no humanity."},{"time":450480,"text":"Even when someone does call for empathy\nand understanding for the other side,"},{"time":454320,"text":"the conversation nearly always devolves"},{"time":456240,"text":"into a debate about\nwho deserves more empathy."},{"time":459720,"text":"And just as I learned to do,"},{"time":461240,"text":"we routinely refuse to acknowledge\nthe flaws in our positions"},{"time":464800,"text":"or the merits in our opponent's."},{"time":467200,"text":"Compromise is anathema."},{"time":469600,"text":"We even target people on our own side\nwhen they dare to question the party line."},{"time":474800,"text":"This path has brought us cruel,\nsniping, deepening polarization,"},{"time":479320,"text":"and even outbreaks of violence."},{"time":481560,"text":"I remember this path."},{"time":483640,"text":"It will not take us where we want to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487080,"text":"What gives me hope is that\nwe can do something about this."},{"time":490560,"text":"The good news is that it's simple,"},{"time":492840,"text":"and the bad news is that it's hard."},{"time":495200,"text":"We have to talk and listen\nto people we disagree with."},{"time":500040,"text":"It's hard because we often can't fathom"},{"time":501960,"text":"how the other side\ncame to their positions."},{"time":504800,"text":"It's hard because righteous indignation,"},{"time":507400,"text":"that sense of certainty\nthat ours is the right side,"},{"time":510600,"text":"is so seductive."},{"time":512919,"text":"It's hard because it means\nextending empathy and compassion"},{"time":516280,"text":"to people who show us\nhostility and contempt."},{"time":519600,"text":"The impulse to respond in kind\nis so tempting,"},{"time":523360,"text":"but that isn't who we want to be."},{"time":525320,"text":"We can resist."},{"time":527000,"text":"And I will always be inspired to do so\nby those people I encountered on Twitter,"},{"time":531480,"text":"apparent enemies\nwho became my beloved friends."},{"time":535200,"text":"And in the case of one particularly\nunderstanding and generous guy,"},{"time":538640,"text":"my husband."},{"time":540800,"text":"There was nothing special\nabout the way I responded to him."},{"time":544960,"text":"What was special was their approach."},{"time":548080,"text":"I thought about it a lot\nover the past few years"},{"time":550680,"text":"and I found four things\nthey did differently"},{"time":553560,"text":"that made real conversation possible."},{"time":557000,"text":"These four steps were small but powerful,"},{"time":559360,"text":"and I do everything I can to employ them\nin difficult conversations today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564240,"text":"The first is don't assume bad intent."},{"time":568240,"text":"My friends on Twitter realized"},{"time":569720,"text":"that even when my words\nwere aggressive and offensive,"},{"time":572680,"text":"I sincerely believed\nI was doing the right thing."},{"time":575600,"text":"Assuming ill motives\nalmost instantly cuts us off"},{"time":578600,"text":"from truly understanding\nwhy someone does and believes as they do."},{"time":582920,"text":"We forget that they're a human being"},{"time":584680,"text":"with a lifetime of experience\nthat shaped their mind,"},{"time":587680,"text":"and we get stuck\non that first wave of anger,"},{"time":590400,"text":"and the conversation has a very hard time\never moving beyond it."},{"time":594800,"text":"But when we assume good or neutral intent,"},{"time":597480,"text":"we give our minds a much stronger\nframework for dialogue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602160,"text":"The second is ask questions."},{"time":605760,"text":"When we engage people\nacross ideological divides,"},{"time":608360,"text":"asking questions\nhelps us map the disconnect"},{"time":610840,"text":"between our differing points of view."},{"time":613200,"text":"That's important because\nwe can't present effective arguments"},{"time":616120,"text":"if we don't understand where\nthe other side is actually coming from"},{"time":620320,"text":"and because it gives them an opportunity\nto point out flaws in our positions."},{"time":625080,"text":"But asking questions\nserves another purpose;"},{"time":627560,"text":"it signals to someone\nthat they're being heard."},{"time":630760,"text":"When my friends on Twitter\nstopped accusing"},{"time":632920,"text":"and started asking questions,"},{"time":634720,"text":"I almost automatically mirrored them."},{"time":637760,"text":"Their questions gave me room to speak,"},{"time":639640,"text":"but they also gave me permission\nto ask them questions"},{"time":643040,"text":"and to truly hear their responses."},{"time":645880,"text":"It fundamentally changed\nthe dynamic of our conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650320,"text":"The third is stay calm."},{"time":653000,"text":"This takes practice and patience,"},{"time":654840,"text":"but it's powerful."},{"time":656720,"text":"At Westboro, I learned not to care\nhow my manner of speaking affected others."},{"time":661040,"text":"I thought my rightness\njustified my rudeness --"},{"time":664120,"text":"harsh tones, raised voices,\ninsults, interruptions --"},{"time":667880,"text":"but that strategy\nis ultimately counterproductive."},{"time":670960,"text":"Dialing up the volume and the snark\nis natural in stressful situations,"},{"time":674760,"text":"but it tends to bring the conversation\nto an unsatisfactory, explosive end."},{"time":680600,"text":"When my husband was still\njust an anonymous Twitter acquaintance,"},{"time":683880,"text":"our discussions frequently\nbecame hard and pointed,"},{"time":686760,"text":"but we always refused to escalate."},{"time":689360,"text":"Instead, he would change the subject."},{"time":691320,"text":"He would tell a joke or recommend a book"},{"time":693560,"text":"or gently excuse himself\nfrom the conversation."},{"time":697560,"text":"We knew the discussion wasn't over,"},{"time":699440,"text":"just paused for a time\nto bring us back to an even keel."},{"time":703600,"text":"People often lament that digital\ncommunication makes us less civil,"},{"time":706800,"text":"but this is one advantage that online\nconversations have over in-person ones."},{"time":711680,"text":"We have a buffer of time and space"},{"time":714320,"text":"between us and the people\nwhose ideas we find so frustrating."},{"time":718280,"text":"We can use that buffer."},{"time":720360,"text":"Instead of lashing out,\nwe can pause, breathe,"},{"time":724080,"text":"change the subject or walk away,"},{"time":726280,"text":"and then come back to it when we're ready."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730200,"text":"And finally ..."},{"time":732760,"text":"make the argument."},{"time":736120,"text":"This might seem obvious,"},{"time":737440,"text":"but one side effect\nof having strong beliefs"},{"time":740040,"text":"is that we sometimes assume"},{"time":741680,"text":"that the value of our position\nis or should be obvious and self-evident,"},{"time":746800,"text":"that we shouldn't\nhave to defend our positions"},{"time":749040,"text":"because they're so clearly right and good"},{"time":752160,"text":"that if someone doesn't get it,\nit's their problem --"},{"time":754760,"text":"that it's not my job to educate them."},{"time":757560,"text":"But if it were that simple,"},{"time":758920,"text":"we would all see things the same way."},{"time":761360,"text":"As kind as my friends on Twitter were,"},{"time":763840,"text":"if they hadn't actually\nmade their arguments,"},{"time":766240,"text":"it would've been so much harder for me\nto see the world in a different way."},{"time":770960,"text":"We are all a product of our upbringing,"},{"time":773400,"text":"and our beliefs reflect our experiences."},{"time":776560,"text":"We can't expect others\nto spontaneously change their own minds."},{"time":780560,"text":"If we want change,"},{"time":782000,"text":"we have to make the case for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785160,"text":"My friends on Twitter didn't abandon\ntheir beliefs or their principles --"},{"time":789240,"text":"only their scorn."},{"time":791240,"text":"They channeled their\ninfinitely justifiable offense"},{"time":794880,"text":"and came to me with pointed questions\ntempered with kindness and humor."},{"time":799880,"text":"They approached me as a human being,"},{"time":802000,"text":"and that was more transformative"},{"time":803600,"text":"than two full decades\nof outrage, disdain and violence."},{"time":808760,"text":"I know that some might not have\nthe time or the energy or the patience"},{"time":812560,"text":"for extensive engagement,"},{"time":813840,"text":"but as difficult as it can be,"},{"time":815920,"text":"reaching out to someone we disagree with"},{"time":818440,"text":"is an option that is\navailable to all of us."},{"time":821280,"text":"And I sincerely believe\nthat we can do hard things,"},{"time":825120,"text":"not just for them\nbut for us and our future."},{"time":828480,"text":"Escalating disgust\nand intractable conflict"},{"time":831000,"text":"are not what we want for ourselves,"},{"time":833160,"text":"or our country"},{"time":834440,"text":"or our next generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837520,"text":"My mom said something to me\na few weeks before I left Westboro,"},{"time":841840,"text":"when I was desperately hoping"},{"time":843280,"text":"there was a way\nI could stay with my family."},{"time":846920,"text":"People I have loved\nwith every pulse of my heart"},{"time":849320,"text":"since even before I was\nthat chubby-cheeked five-year-old,"},{"time":852680,"text":"standing on a picket line\nholding a sign I couldn't read."},{"time":856160,"text":"She said, \"You're just a human being,"},{"time":858840,"text":"my dear, sweet child.\""},{"time":861760,"text":"She was asking me to be humble --"},{"time":864040,"text":"not to question\nbut to trust God and my elders."},{"time":867960,"text":"But to me, she was missing\nthe bigger picture --"},{"time":871520,"text":"that we're all just human beings."},{"time":874120,"text":"That we should be guided\nby that most basic fact,"},{"time":877080,"text":"and approach one another\nwith generosity and compassion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880320,"text":"Each one of us\ncontributes to the communities"},{"time":882640,"text":"and the cultures and the societies\nthat we make up."},{"time":886000,"text":"The end of this spiral of rage and blame\nbegins with one person"},{"time":890680,"text":"who refuses to indulge\nthese destructive, seductive impulses."},{"time":895920,"text":"We just have to decide\nthat it's going to start with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898960,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900200,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}